<h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-100 mb-6">Agents & Accessories</h1>

<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-6">
  Botster uses two types of session definitions: <strong class="text-zinc-200">agents</strong> (AI-driven PTY sessions)
  and <strong class="text-zinc-200">accessories</strong> (plain PTY sessions like dev servers or log tailers).
</p>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Directory layout</h2>
<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-4">
  Session definitions live in the
  <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">agents/</code> and
  <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">accessories/</code>
  directories at either the device or repo level:
</p>
<pre class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300 font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>~/.botster/agents/claude/             # Device-level agent
~/.botster/accessories/rails-server/  # Device-level accessory
your-repo/.botster/agents/claude/     # Repo-level agent (overrides device)</code></pre>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Agent selection</h2>
<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-4">
  If only one agent config exists, it's selected automatically. With multiple agent configs, you choose one when creating an agent:
</p>
<pre class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300 font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>create_agent(agent_name: "claude")</code></pre>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Config resolution</h2>
<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-4">
  Botster merges configuration from two layers, repo wins on collision:
</p>
<ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-zinc-400 space-y-1">
  <li>Device (<code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">~/.botster/</code>)</li>
  <li>Repo (<code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">{repo}/.botster/</code>) &mdash; highest priority</li>
</ol>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Workspaces</h2>
<p class="text-zinc-400 mb-4">
  Workspace manifests in <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">workspaces/</code>
  define which agents and accessories auto-spawn together:
</p>
<pre class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm text-zinc-300 font-mono overflow-x-auto mb-6"><code>~/.botster/workspaces/dev.json
your-repo/.botster/workspaces/full-stack.json</code></pre>

<h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-200 mt-8 mb-3">Migration from profiles</h2>
<p class="text-zinc-400">
  If you have an existing <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">shared/</code> and
  <code class="text-zinc-300 bg-zinc-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">profiles/</code> directory structure,
  Botster auto-migrates to the new layout on first run. No manual changes needed.
</p>
